posts.name: SndMndBdy
posts.cooked:
A couple of things to check:

-Have you updated the firmware on the SparkMax in question? There is new firmware for this season -Have you inadvertently created two instances of a SparkMax in code, both with the same CAN ID? -Do you have any problematic CAN wiring ?  Check all of your connections to make sure that they all look good and are yellow-to yellow and green-to-green -Connect a USB cable to the laptop and the SparkMax, and look at it in the Rev Hardware client to see if there are any error messages.

posts.name: Val
posts.cooked:
so this is my best guess, It looks like an error when configuring the conversion rates “parameter Invalid error” = it tried to set a “parameter” and ran into an issue the parameter ID is 113 which based on Rev’s documentation is the velocity conversion factor. The ID is #8 because that’s the first motor of the first module that yagsl is initializing. based on the YAGSL docs they want a “Drive / Angle Composition” instead of a raw number which you have in your configs your config:

our config as an example (which technically runs, still working out some kinks but the code successfully initializes)

I reccomend using the Swerve Bring-up checklist which yagsl mentions in their configuration docs to get the numbers! I hope this helps!
